				<ol class="- topic/ol ">
					<li class="- topic/li ">
						<p class="- topic/p ">TABLE 1(iv).  To facilitate planning for SAF/AQC Clearance approvals, SCOs must use the <xref href="https://cs2.eis.af.mil/sites/10059/afcc/knowledge_center/Quarterly%20Updates/Forms/AllItems.aspx"
    								scope="external"
    								format="aspx"
    								class="- topic/xref ">
								<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">reporting tool</u>
							</xref> to project SAF/AQC Clearance approvals. <ol class="- topic/ol ">
								<li outputclass="List 2"
  									class="- topic/li ">
									<p outputclass="List 2"
 										class="- topic/p ">(2)  For PEO and Enterprise contracting, business and contract clearance are required for actions greater than or equal to $5M. </p>
								</li>
								<li outputclass="List 2"
  									class="- topic/li ">
									<p outputclass="List 2"
 										class="- topic/p ">(3)  For Operational contracting, business and contract clearance are required for actions greater than or equal to $3M.  Contracting squadrons or their equivalents will assign subordinate thresholds within their organization with approval authority at least one level above the CO for contract actions greater than $500K. On a case-by-case basis, the SCO may review a specific contract action below the established threshold in order to ensure compliance with applicable standards and practices. The SCO may lower the threshold below $3M or rescind a previously granted increased threshold for a subordinate contracting unit.   INTERIM CHANGE:  See <xref href="https://cs2.eis.af.mil/sites/10059/afcc/knowledge_center/Documents/Contracting_Memos/Policy/20-C-02.pdf"
    											scope="external"
    											format="pdf"
    											class="- topic/xref ">
											<ph class="- topic/ph ">
												<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Policy Memo</u>
												<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u "> 20-C-02</u>
											</ph>
										</xref>.</p>
								</li>
								<li outputclass="List 2"
  									class="- topic/li ">
									<p outputclass="List 2"
 										class="- topic/p ">(4) SCOs are responsible for ensuring all further delegations of clearance approval authorities are included in the PGI.  </p>
								</li>
								<li outputclass="List 2"
  									class="- topic/li ">
									<p outputclass="List 2"
 										class="- topic/p ">(5)  When a contracting official is the Source Selection Authority (SSA) for a particular acquisition, the CAA must be a level above the contracting official.  If the SCO or their deputy is the SSA, the CAA for that acquisition must be the DAS(C)/ADAS(C).   <xref href="https://cs2.eis.af.mil/sites/10059/afcc/knowledge_center/templates/request_for_clearance.pdf"
    											scope="external"
    											format="pdf"
    											class="- topic/xref ">
											<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Clearance requests</u>
										</xref> must be sent to <xref href="mailto:SAF.AQ.SAF-AQC.Workflow@us.af.mil"
    											scope="external"
    											format="mailto"
    											class="- topic/xref ">
											<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">SAF/AQC</u>
										</xref> for approval by the DAS(C)/ADAS(C).</p>
								</li>
